ksdk:manifest.name: SDK version 2.2.0 package for MKL16Z64xxx4 device
ksdk:manifest.brief: This is SDK version 2.2.0 manifest file. It describes the content of the SDK version 2.2.0 package for MKL16Z64xxx4 device and additional settings for tools that support SDK version 2.2.0

board.name: FRDM-KL26Z
board.description: FRDM-KL26Z: Freedom Development Platform for Kinetis KL16 and KL26 MCUs (up to 128 KB Flash)

specific.content:
The Freedom KL26Z is an ultra-low-cost development platform for Kinetis速 L series KL16 and KL26 MCUs (up to 128 KB Flash and up to 64-pin packages) built on ARM速 Cortex速-M0+ processor.
  • Easy access to MCU I/O, battery-ready, low-power operation, a standard-based form factor with expansion board options and a built-in debug interface for flash programming and run-control
  • Supported by a range of NXP速 and third-party development software
  • For development tools for KL16 and KL26 with 256 KB Flash or greater than 64-pin packages, use FRDM-KL46Z and TWR-KL46Z48M

device.name: MKL16Z4
device.description: KL1x: Kinetis速 KL1x-48 MHz, Mainstream Small Ultra-Low Power Microcontrollers (MCUs) based on ARM速 Cortex速-M0+ Core

specific.content:
The Kinetis速 KL1x is a general purpose ultra-low-power MCU family, providing additional memory, communications and analog peripheral options beyond those offered in the Kinetis KL0x MCU family.
The KL1x MCU family is compatible with Kinetis K10 MCUs (based on ARM速 Cortex速-M4) and with all other Kinetis KL1x, KL2x, KL3x and KL4x series MCUs, providing a migration path to higher performance and feature integration.

device.name: MKL26Z4
device.description: KL2x: Kinetis速 KL2x-48 MHz, USB Ultra-Low-Power Microcontrollers (MCUs) based on ARM速 Cortex速-M0+ Core

specific.content:
The Kinetis速 KL2x is an ultra-low-power MCU family that adds a full-speed USB 2.0 On-the-Go (OTG) controller or a full-speed crystal-less USB 2.0 device controller in addition to the Kinetis KL1x series.
The Kinetis KL2x MCU family is compatible with Kinetis K20 MCUs (based on ARM速 Cortex速-M4), and with all other Kinetis KL1x, KL2x, KL3x, and KL4x series MCUs, providing a migration path to lower and higher performance and feature integration.
